Vice President Biden's spokesperson, Elizabeth Alexander, released a statement on March 16, 2009, regarding the surgery of the Vice President's mother, Catherine Eugenia "Jean" Biden. Mrs. Biden underwent surgery at the Hospital of the University of Pennsylvania for a hip fracture. The surgery was successful, and she is recovering well and in stable condition. Dr. Samir Mehta, the chief of the Division of Orthopaedic Trauma at the hospital, performed the surgery, which involved applying a plate and screw device to Mrs. Biden's hip. Dr. Mehta is pleased with the outcome of the surgery.